<SLUG> BC-CLINTON-MORRIS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLINTON WANTED TO TELL, DICK MORRIS SAYS 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 By DAVID STOUT   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The way Dick Morris recalls that fateful Wednesday,
Jan. 21, President Clinton seemed to want to tell the country right
away that he had made a mistake with Monica Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
   That was the day news reports began saying the Whitewater
independent counsel, Kenneth Starr, was investigating whether the
president had had a sexual relationship with the former White House
intern and then tried to cover it up.
</P>
<P>
   That morning, Clinton told him, ``You know,'' he said, ``ever
since I was elected president, I've tried to stop this kind of
thing and not do this stuff. But I just slipped up with this
girl,'' Morris said on Tuesday night. At another point, the
president told him, ``I didn't do what they said I did, but I did
something.'' But Morris said the president denied that he had urged
Ms. Lewinsky to lie under oath.
</P>
<P>
   Morris, a political consultant, said he had not pressed Clinton
on what ``something'' meant, thinking it better that he not be
told. But he said he sensed strongly that Clinton, whom he knew
well from having advised him in the past, wanted to unburden
himself to the people. So why didn't he, instead of waiting for
seven months?
</P>
<P>
   As Morris said Tuesday night on Fox News, Clinton may have felt
worried by the findings of a confidential poll by Morris on Jan.
21.
</P>
<P>
   At 11:30 that night, Morris said, he called Clinton and told him
the poll showed the American people would forgive adultery. But, he
told the president, ``If they feel that you lied under oath, and
they feel that you suborned perjury in any way, you're cooked. They
want you out. Forgiveness won't work.''
</P>
<P>
   Four days earlier, in a deposition he gave in connection with
the sexual-misconduct lawsuit filed against Clinton by Paula Jones,
Clinton testified that he had not had a sexual relationship with
Ms. Lewinsky.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
