<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ If I were Bill and if the Republicans
want details, I'd give them lots. Sort of like this, ``Well, Monica
was at the bookstore and along with an embossed leather and
parchment copy of the poems of Elizabeth Barrett Browning, she got
a Best Parts Version of the Kama Sutra. We started with `Crane
Walks on Misty Lake,' which begins with the woman putting her left
foot on your forehead and ends with the walking part, which is
pretty tough if you're 52. I really started thinking I was doing
the wrong thing morally at Chapter 72, `Muskrat in Bamboo Grove.'
'' (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
