said it will buy the South Florida Newspaper Network, a chain of
weekly papers that circulate from Miami to Vero Beach. The company
would not reveal the sale price. Sun-Sentinel Co. President Bob
Gremillion said the purchase helps speed the company's growth,
expands the number of potential readers and advertisers, and
provides a new place to promote its newspaper and other
publications. (Plunkett, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
