<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ If I were Bill and if the Republicans
want details, I'd give them lots. Sort of like this, ``Well, Monica
was at the bookstore and along with an embossed leather and
parchment copy of the poems of Elizabeth Barrett Browning, she got
a Best Parts Version of the Kama Sutra. We started with `Crane
Walks on Misty Lake,' which begins with the woman putting her left
foot on your forehead and ends with the walking part, which is
pretty tough if you're 52. I really started thinking I was doing
the wrong thing morally at Chapter 72, `Muskrat in Bamboo Grove.'
'' (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ MOSCOW _ On the way into Moscow from the
airport, my old friend and interpreter Pavlik was telling me how
much things had changed. Lots of crime in Moscow now, he said. But
not to worry. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ Texas is drawing raves nationally for dealing
with intractable academic deficiencies using a content-linked
measuring device and insisting on accountability. The credit is
deserved. But when content and accountability are affixed so
tightly to the basics, students who already have a handle on those
basics are fixed in place, brain cells frying in the deep fat of
boredom. (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ Yes, there's going to be a wedding with all the
trimmings. The table arrangements. The old railroad lanterns that
are being rewired and used for lights. The tiny bottles of bubbles.
The carefully stenciled terra cotta pots with the pink impatiens
inside. It's all going to come together Labor Day weekend, God
willing. And it appears He is. For this is a match we thought might
never happen. (Minor, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ Grabitis is treatable. So I don't think Bill
Clinton should be impeached. Instead, I say he should be sentenced
to a cold shower three times a day, or perhaps a daily dip in Lake
Michigan during winter. The other thing that could be done to cure
the president would be to make him wear a pair of huge barbecue
mitts 24 hours a day. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
8/18.
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ When it comes to lying, Clinton is one of the
best. (Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald.) MOVED 8/18.
</P>
<P>
   CSIBLEY-COLUMN _ A writer friend of mine says when you're
working on a book, some of the best ideas you'll ever have come to
you in the middle of the night. (Sibley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 8/18.
</P>
