<P>
   TEXAS-AQUIFER _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The southern portion of the
Edwards Aquifer, a vast underground water sourcethat provides
drinking water to San Antonio and surrounding cities, is finally
starting to refill. But the story is different in the Austin area.
The Barton Springs section of the Edwards Aquifer, which is
separate from the section that runs under San Antonio, has received
little recharge from the lighter rains that have fallen here.
(Thatcher, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
