<TEXT>
<P>
   What happens when celebrities are caught in compromising
situations while wearing designer labels with which they have no
commercial association?
</P>
<P>
   For example, Hugh Grant was wearing a Tommy Hilfiger cap when he
was arrested for soliciting a prostitute, and Monica Lewinsky was
wearing a Donna Karan beret when she was photographed with
President Bill Clinton in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
   In an article titled ``From Monica to O.J., Celebrity Endorsers
Can Be Risky Business'' from a recent issue of Women's Wear Daily,
reporter Eric Wilson talks with company executives who discuss the
impact of these unplanned product placements. This 1,000-word
article is available for one-shot purchase from The New York Times
Syndicate.
</P>
