worst he is threatened with is a six-month suspended sentence.
</P>
<P>
   Guilio Andreotti, another former prime minister, has been on
trial for the past four years accused of collusion with the Mafia.
He is 79 and analysts have predicted the case won't be wound up
during his lifetime.
</P>
<P>
   ``Even when they are arrested and put on trial, which is seldom,
powerful European politicians rarely suffer severe consequences,''
Camus noted. ``The system works like that.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
