<SLUG> BC-STOOGES-CONVENTION-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VICTIM OF SOICUMSTANCE?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; Awright, you knuckleheads! This here is the very
first Three Stooges convention ever held on the West Coast, y'hear?
</P>
<P>
   This weekend's wacky event _ staged by Comedy III Entertainment
Inc., which represents heirs of the slapstick trio _ will include
Stooges' films, pie fights, contests, celebrity appearances
(including some original cast members), tributes and memorabilia.
Participants will have a chance to become a Stooge, have a photo
taken with the Stooges or take part in one of their short films.
</P>
<P>
   Opening ceremonies will be hosted by funnyman disc jockey and
Stooge lover Gary Owens.
</P>
<P>
   It'll run from 2 to 7 p.m. Friday, and 10 a.m. to 6 p.m.
Saturday and Sunday at the Burbank Airport Hilton Hotel and
Convention Center, 2500 Hollywood Way, Burbank. Admission is $25
per day, with kids under 6 admitted free; Friday admission is half
price.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call (888) 878-6643.
</P>
</TEXT>
