his resignation and plans to push ahead with his political agenda
during the last two years of his term, his spokesman said
Wednesday. By John M. Broder. (early summary from wires)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-POLITICS (Washington) _ The continuing political fallout
from President Clinton's speech; comparing reaction from the public
at large to the views of political activists. By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   With: CLINTON-HEARTLAND.
</P>
