</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-WEEKEND20-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This Weekend on TV
 &HT;    By Lyle V. Harris
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRIDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Midnight Run'' (1988) 10:15 p.m. EDT on TNT _ Great buddy
movie, road comedy with Robert De Niro starring as a roughneck skip
tracer who tracks down a nebbish accountant (Charles Grodin) wanted
by the feds and the mob.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Relic'' (1997) 8 p.m. EDT on HBO _ Better-than-scary
horror movie about a swanky exhibit opening at a Philadelphia
museum that's disrupted when a monster starts chowing down on the
well-heeled guests. Tom Sizemore is fun to watch as the been-there,
done-that cop tracking the beast.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The American President'' (1995) 8:05 EDT on TBS _ Need a
lighthearted diversion from the ongoing White House mess? Check out
Michael Douglas as the widowed commander in chief who falls for
plucky political operative Annette Bening while fending off charges
of immorality from an ultra-right-wing senator played by Richard
Dreyfuss.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Lusitania: Murder on the Atlantic'' 9 p.m. EDT on A&AMP;E _ If
you're starting to suffer from Leo-mania and Titanic-itis, this
documentary about a less celebrated maritime tragedy might be the
cure. About 1,200 people died when the luxury liner was torpedoed
and sunk during a surprise
</P>
<P>
   U-boat attack off the coast of Ireland in 1915.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Rat Pack'' (1998) 9 p.m. EDT on HBO _ Most of them have
left us for that big Vegas nightclub in the sky, but this
unauthorized docudrama chronicles the fast-living, hard-drinking,
babe-loving Kings of Swing: Frank Sinatra (Ray Liotta), Dean Martin
(Joe Mantegna) and Sammy Davis Jr. (Don Cheadle). Also hanging out
are Joey Bishop (Bobby Slayton) and Peter Lawford (Angus
Macfadyen).
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Hard Boiled'' 10:35 p.m. EDT on The Movie Channel _ Flashy
and violent cult hit starring sexy tough guy Chow Yun-Fat as a good
guy with a bad attitude and plenty of firepower.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Storm of the Century'' 9 p.m. EDT on TLC _ A look at the
1991 storm that hit the New England coast with 100-mph winds and
100-foot waves whipped up by a freakish, and deadly, weather
pattern. Said one rescue worker who survived it: ``With all of
today's technology, we were still at the mercy of Mother Nature.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``The Baby Dance'' (1998) 9 p.m. EDT on Showtime _ Based on
the award-winning stage play of the same name, and starring Laura
Dern as a trailer-living mother who agrees to let a rich, infertile
woman (Stockard Channing) and her husband adopt her baby.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
