<P>
   COLOMBIA-CROPS (San Jose De Guaviare, Colombia) _ Here in the
coca growing heartland of Colombia, where the U.S.-backed war on
drugs is fought with herbicides and helicopter gunships, coca
growers remain skeptical of the new Colombian president's plan
``Marshall Plan'' to end drug growing in rural areas by bringing in
electricity, water and roads. Embittered by years of fumigation and
confrontation with government authorities, they doubt the talk of a
Marshall Plan would go anywhere. Any plan's first obstacle may well
lie with the growers themselves. By Diana Jean Schemo. 1,200 words.
</P>
