<P>
   AUS-PAUL-BEGALA _ AUSTIN _For Paul Begala, who is so practiced
at standing in fires that he could be a swami, this has been the
week from hell. While he's made defending Bill Clinton almost an
art form, he'd done it in the belief that Clinton was telling the
truth. But Clinton's admission Monday that he'd lied, that he
really did have a relationship with former White House intern
Monica Lewinsky, had to be a cruel slap in the face. Begala is the
man who, perhaps more than any other, has stood out front and taken
the heat for the leader of the Western World. Begala did it because
he's a believer. It may sound corny, but it's true: he believes in
democracy, he believes in people, he believes in God, he believes
in the truth _ all with a passion that is electric and contagious.
(McNeely, Austin American Statesman)
</P>
