<SLUG> BC-STYLE-CHECKLIST-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    10 MUST-HAVES FOR COLLEGE
 &HT;    (EMBARGOED UNTIL AUGUST 23: DO NOT USE BEFORE THEN)
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The time has come for freshmen entering college to consider two
crucial questions: what to major in and what to wear.
</P>
<P>
   Neither one's easily answered.
</P>
<P>
   But the thought process involved in the former has applications
for the latter as well.
</P>
<P>
   Picking a major and packing for college are both best achieved
by covering the basics. Comfort, practicality and versatility are
qualities to look for in campus wear. But choosing clothes that
make sense doesn't necessarily obviate (oh, look it up)
opportunities for students to showcase their individual sense of
style.
</P>
<P>
   The checklist below should serve as a guide to those students
with more doubt in their minds than time on their hands to get
packed. Unlike some guides, this one doesn't demand that you ``stay
with the group.'' Just don't stray so far from it that you wind up
looking and feeling lost.
</P>
<P>
   MEN
</P>
<P>
   The ``Gilligan'' hat: For when you really need a haircut, or the
one you got from a new barber is too laughable for words. ($28 from
Gadzooks)
</P>
<P>
   The blue blazer: For fraternity soirees or that ``chat'' with
the dean. ($230 from Brooks Brothers)
</P>
<P>
   The messenger-style shoulder bag: Backpacks are for book-laden
dorks.
</P>
<P>
   ($17 from the Gap Outlet)
</P>
<P>
   Vests: It doesn't take much to dress up a T-shirt ($25 by Point
Zero, from Uptons.)
</P>
<P>
   Dark denim: Fewer visible stains equal fewer trips to the
laundry room. ($20 from the Gap Outlet)
</P>
<P>
   WOMEN
</P>
<P>
   Hair jewelry: For days when that just-got-out-of-bed look isn't
intentional. (``Chopsticks'' and ponytail clip, both $4 from
Claire's Boutique)
</P>
<P>
   The little black dress: When asked out on a date, it's OK to act
surprised, not be caught off-guard. ($50 from the BCBG Outlet)
</P>
<P>
   The messenger-style shoulder bag: Better-looking and better for
you than backpacks. ($17 from the Gap Outlet)
</P>
<P>
   Dark denim: They've got an edge in style over the faded jeans of
old. ($20 from the Gap Outlet)
</P>
<P>
   High-heeled sneakers: For a needed lift when you're on the go,
go, go.
</P>
<P>
   ($50 by Sbicca, from Uptons.)
</P>
<P>
   Just trust us on this one. (Panties $3 each, sheer bra/panty set
$5.50, all from the L'eggs-Hanes-Bali-Playtex Outlet)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
