<SLUG> BC-FIDELITY-MCGOVERN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FIDELITY NAMES MCGOVERN SENIOR OPERATIONS OFFICER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By LYNNLEY BROWNING  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Fidelity Investments Wednesday named Gail McGovern, AT&AMP;T Corp.'s
highest ranking female executive, as senior operations officer at
the mutual fund firm's sales and distribution unit for individual
and brokerage clients.
</P>
<P>
   McGovern, 46, was executive vice president of AT&AMP;T's consumer
markets division, where she oversaw worldwide consumer sales and
marketing for the telecommunications giant at a time of increased
competition. She faces a similar task at Boston-based Fidelity,
which is working to maintain and build market share amid stiffer
competition in the fund industry.
</P>
<P>
   McGovern reports to J. Gary Burkhead, who oversees Fidelity's
Personal Investments and Brokerage Group, the sales and
distribution unit. ``Her first challenge will be to bring new
dimensions to the way we reach, touch, and hold our 6.3 million
retail customers,'' Burkhead said. The group oversees $274 billion
in managed assets out of Fidelity's total $693 billion.
</P>
<P>
   The appointment is the latest step by Fidelity, already the
nation's largest provider of employee-sponsored retirement plans,
to court individual customers. Fidelity's marketing head, Stephen
A. Cone, who was appointed in February, is also revamping the
firm's approach to one of its core consumer segments.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-19-98 1831EDT &QL; 
