<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
LOBBY (Phoenix) - Arizona Republican leaders have laid out a battle
plan to retain control of the state Senate, giving lobbyists
``marching orders'' to raise money for GOP candidates in three
swing races. The goal, according to sources familiar with the
discussions, was to name coordinators in the lobbying community who
could direct campaign donations and assistance from both lobbyists
and political action committees from the industries they represent.
Critics say the memo obtained by teh Arizona Republic confirms what
many always suspected: That special interests have a stranglehold
on the legislative process in Arizona. By
</P>
<P>
   CHRIS MOESER.
</P>
<P>
   Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - Some members of Congress are so upset
with President Bill Clinton they believe he should be impeached and
removed from office. I, for one, am willing to go along with that.
Right after they indict the chairman of R.J. Reynolds Along with
the heads of Philip Morris, U.S. Tobacco, Lorillard Tobacco,
Liggett Group, Brown &AMP; Williamson Tobacco and American Tobacco. By
E.J.MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MANGO (Undated) - Now is the time to experiment with this lucious
hot-climate fruit, when they're three for $1 in stores. In April in
Thailand, Mangoes with Sticky Rice becomes the national dessert,
sold on the streets. Withrecipes and MANGOSIDE, PHOTOS. By JUDY
WALKER. Stories moved in the ``D'' category. &QL; 
