<P>
   HEARST-HASSLE (Los Angeles) _ Nearly five decades after William
Randolph Hearst died, his descendants and trustees are still
squabbling over the media giant's will. By Peter Hartlaub. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
