<P>
   CHIPMAKERS-EARNINGS (San Francisco) _ Two computer-chip makers _
LSI Logic and National Semiconductor _ said Wednesday that they
expected sharply lower quarterly results because of Asia's economic
crisis, and a third _ Analog Devices _ said its quarterly net
earnings fell 81 percent. By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Display)
</P>
<P>
   OPTIONS-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ As more and more companies
choose to reprice their employee stock-option plans, criticism of
the practice grows increasingly vocal. Shareholder activist groups
say option repricings are inherently unfair. Now a tentative
decision reached by the Financial Accounting Standards Board last
week may be the beginning of the end of repricings. By Gretchen
Morgenson.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic showing how new accounting rule would affect
stock options is being sent to NYT graphic clients. Non-subscribers
can make individual purchase by calling (888) 603-1036 or (888)
346-9867.) &QL;
