irregularities were recently discovered. By Melody Petersen.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom Center)
</P>
<P>
   JOBS-DISPLACEMENT (Undated) _ The most comprehensive survey of
permanent layoffs in the United States finds that in the last three
years a smaller percentage of workers were downsized than in any
other period in this decade. But the layoff rate is still
significantly higher than in the 1980s, and women are laid off
almost as often as men. By Louis Uchitelle.
</P>
