   (Bottom Right)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ A federal appeals court ruled
Wednesday that pretrial questioning of Bill Gates and 16 other
Microsoft Corp. executives could be undertaken behind closed doors,
overruling a lower-court judge who had ruled that the depositions
had to be public. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
