<P>
   CREDIT (New York) _ Treasury bond prices were little changed
Wednesday, with the dollar continuing to slide against the yen.
This was attributed to talk of possible intervention by the
Japanese to aid the yen. Also a report of stronger-than-expected
housing starts gave investors little incentive to buy bonds with
yields near record lows. By Robert Hurtado.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved.)
</P>
<P>
   HIGH-FASHION-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Fashion advertising _
especially in the all-important fall season, a sort of Christmas
for publishers of fashion magazines _ has almost exclusively used
images of fantasy. But now there are signs that fashion is trying
to add a little realism. By Jennifer Steinhauer.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET.)
</P>
