<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Baseball Dreamers: The Road to Turner Field
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ABOUT THE SERIES
</P>
<P>
   The journey to the major leagues is a long and difficult one
that ends in unfulfilled dreams for most baseball hopefuls. In an
eight-part series, Journal-Constitution staff writers Guy Curtright
and Jack Wilkinson, with staff photographer Ben Gray, take a road
trip through the Atlanta Braves farm system.
</P>
<P>
   _ Aug. 16: Dominican Summer League.
</P>
<P>
   _ Monday: Gulf Coast League.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tuesday: Appalachian League.
</P>
<P>
   _ Wednesday: Northwest League.
</P>
<P>
   _ Today: South Atlantic League.
</P>
<P>
   _ Friday: Carolina League. Paul Runge, a former Braves
infielder, knows that managing in the minors is about more than
wins and losses.
</P>
<P>
   _ Saturday: Southern League. Greenville outfielder George
Lombard is happy that August has arrived and trade rumors have
ended.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sunday: International League. At Richmond, young prospects
like Bruce Chen mix with veterans such as Gene Schall trying for
one more shot at the majors.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
