<HEADLINE>
N.Y. TIMES CO. TO BUY BACK MORE SHARES 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The New York Times Co. said Wednesday that its board
had authorized spending as much as $575 million to buy back
additional shares of its class A common stock. So far this year the
company has bought about 6 million shares for $201.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   The shares, which touched a 52-week high of $40.6875 on July 6,
closed Wednesday at $30.75, down 18.75 cents, on the New York Stock
Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
