people, sitting snugly in inner tubes - across a flat,
1,300-foot-long surface. Water gets sucked into grates positioned
every couple of hundred feet along the floor of the river, where it
travels via large pipes to one of three pumping stations in the
park. (Maxine Hicks/New York Times Photo)
