<SLUG> BC-RAC-SARATOGA-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PRIME DIRECTIVE OPENS EYES 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. _ It isn't for nothing that D.Wayne Lukas
is known as the master of 2-year-old horses. Since 1984, he has
trained 24 winners of Saratoga's prestigious juvenile stakes for
colts and fillies.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday in the Saratoga Special, Lukas saddled another
aspiring winner: Tactical Cat, a gray son of the legendary Storm
Cat. Tactical Cat, ridden by Jerry Bailey, the best in the
business, went off as the 1-5 favorite and was expected to dominate
the small field of four. But he labored and finished third while
Prime Directive stole the show, winning by 5{ lengths over Silk
Broker.
</P>
<P>
   Prime Directive was racing last behind a fast pace: the
quarter-mile in 21 4/5 seconds, the half-mile in 45 2/5. With a
quarter of a mile left, he made his move, flew past his three
rivals and seized the lead. He ran the six and a half furlongs in
1:17, paid $9.90 for a $2 bet to win and went home with $90,000 for
his owner, Noreen Carpenito.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
